  "prompt": "Is there any software that counts wifi speed and usage?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several software applications and tools available that can help you monitor both Wi-Fi speed and usage. Here are a few options:\n\n1. **NetSpeedMonitor:** This is a Windows-based tool that displays your internet speed in your taskbar, allowing you to monitor upload and download speeds in real-time.\n\n2. **GlassWire:** GlassWire is a network monitoring tool that provides detailed reports on bandwidth usage by application and also monitors network activity for any unusual behavior. It can show you real-time data usage statistics and can alert you about various network events.\n\n3. **Wireshark:** Although primarily a network protocol analyzer, Wireshark can also be used for monitoring and analyzing detailed network usage data.\n\n4. **BitMeter OS:** This is an open-source bandwidth meter that works across various platforms, allowing you to monitor your internet speed and usage both in real-time and over time.\n\n5. **NetWorx:** This is a versatile tool that can track your internet usage, test your connection speed, and provide detailed reports about your Wi-Fi usage.\n\n6. **Speedtest by Ookla:** While it's mainly used for testing your internet connection's speed, the Speedtest app and web service can give you a quick measure of your Wi-Fi network's performance.\n\n7. **DU Meter:** This software provides detailed reports and real-time alerts for bandwidth usage. It can also set up alerts to ensure you stay within your data limits.\n\n8. **PRTG Network Monitor:** This is a more advanced network monitoring tool that not only measures bandwidth usage but also monitors various aspects of network health.\n\nEach of these tools has its own strengths and can be chosen based on your specific needs, such as ease of use, depth of analytics, platform compatibility, and whether you need real-time data or historical reports.",
